00:47:36,360 --> 00:47:38,920
If we don't, they'll tear us to pieces.

707
00:47:38,960 --> 00:47:41,713
And that will exacerbate things for all of us.

708
00:47:41,760 --> 00:47:44,513
- Shaun...
- This is not about you and me.

709
00:47:44,560 --> 00:47:46,516
This is about survival.

710
00:47:46,560 --> 00:47:50,394
We need to be somewhere more secure,
somewhere we can stay alive.

711
00:47:50,440 --> 00:47:52,590
- We're with you, Shaun.
- What?

712
00:47:52,640 --> 00:47:55,279
- We're with you.
- I'm not going out there.

713
00:47:55,320 --> 00:47:59,916
Daffs! I don't want to be torn to pieces
and if you think about it, neither do you.

714
00:47:59,960 --> 00:48:02,599
- I'm not going if Lizzie's not going.
- She's going.

715
00:48:02,640 --> 00:48:04,756
- I'm not staying by myself.
- You're going, aren't you?

716
00:48:04,800 --> 00:48:06,791
- Lizzie?
- Liz?

717
00:48:11,360 --> 00:48:14,557
- All right, Flash, what's your plan?
- Great. I've got a car

718
00:48:14,600 --> 00:48:18,149
but it's gonna be a bit cramped now.
Has anyone got transport?

719
00:48:18,200 --> 00:48:20,156
- Yes!
- Great. Where?

720
00:48:20,200 --> 00:48:22,953
Oh, no. Well, I've passed my test.

721
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:24,194
David?

722
00:48:24,240 --> 00:48:27,676
I don't see the point
of owning a car in London.

723
00:48:27,720 --> 00:48:30,359
Look, just get any blunt objects together.

724
00:48:30,400 --> 00:48:33,119
If you get cornered,
bash them in the head.

725
00:48:33,160 --> 00:48:35,799
Keep together, stay sharp and follow me.

726
00:48:35,840 --> 00:48:38,149
So, what's the plan, then?

727
00:48:38,200 --> 00:48:40,475
We're going to the Winchester.

728
00:48:44,360 --> 00:48:46,157
OK? Let's go.

729
00:49:01,600 --> 00:49:03,636
- Come on.
- Where's the car?

730
00:49:03,680 --> 00:49:06,717
(Horn beeps, tyres screech)

731
00:49:08,000 --> 00:49:10,116
What's up, niggaz?

732
00:49:14,600 --> 00:49:18,513
Apologies for the cramped conditions.
Di, stay on David's lap.

733
00:49:18,560 --> 00:49:21,518
Philip, hang in there, OK?
Ed, get there fast.

734
00:49:21,560 --> 00:49:23,755
And, Mum, this is Liz. Liz, Mum.

735
00:49:23,800 --> 00:49:25,631
(Both) Hello.

736
00:49:26,920 --> 00:49:30,071
(# 80s Matchbox B-Line Disaster:
Mister Mental)

737
00:49:31,360 --> 00:49:33,715
Ed, be careful.

738
00:49:33,760 --> 00:49:35,830
- Is your dad all right?
- He's not my dad.

739
00:49:35,880 --> 00:49:38,269
- He's bleeding.
- I know! Ed, be careful.

740
00:49:38,320 --> 00:49:40,914
Thought you wanted to get there fast?

741
00:49:41,360 --> 00:49:44,397
I want to get there in one piece!
Why are we going this way?

742
00:49:44,440 --> 00:49:46,431
Chill out, it's a short cut.

743
00:49:46,480 --> 00:49:49,438
- That road goes to the Winchester.
- Shaun...

744
00:49:49,480 --> 00:49:53,632
- Liz, please!
- I don't understand why the Winchester?

745
00:49:53,680 --> 00:49:56,717
- It's a pub, it's safe, it's secure.
- They know us.

746
00:49:56,760 --> 00:50:00,673
- What makes it so secure?
- It's got big heavy doors and deadbolts.

747
00:50:00,720 --> 00:50:02,551
And there's a rifle above the bar.

748
00:50:02,600 --> 00:50:07,071
- I would think that's deactivated.
- It's not. John's connected. Big Al says so.

749
00:50:07,120 --> 00:50:09,156
Big Al also says dogs can't look up.

750
00:50:09,200 --> 00:50:10,633
- They can't.
- Can't they?

751
00:50:10,680 --> 00:50:12,716
- Of course they can!
- Are you sure?

752
00:50:12,760 --> 00:50:16,150
Yes! The pub is the right place to go.
Everything is gonna be fine.

753
00:50:16,200 --> 00:50:18,555
- Shaun...
- I turned it off, all right?

754
00:50:18,600 --> 00:50:20,716
- (Mumbles)
- What?

755
00:50:20,760 --> 00:50:23,957
- Being a father, it's not easy.
- What?

756
00:50:24,480 --> 00:50:28,678
You were 12 when I met you,
you'd already grown up so much.

757
00:50:28,720 --> 00:50:34,511
I just wanted you to be strong
and not give up because you lost your dad.

758
00:50:35,560 --> 00:50:40,873
- Philip, you don't have to explain.
- No, I do. I always loved you, Shaun.

759
00:50:40,920 --> 00:50:45,516
And I always thought
you had it in you to do well.

760
00:50:45,560 --> 00:50:49,712
You just need...m-motivation.

761
00:50:49,760 --> 00:50:52,228
Somebody to look up to and...

762
00:50:55,120 --> 00:50:57,111
I thought it could be me.

763
00:50:58,600 --> 00:51:01,478
Would you just...take care of your mum?

764
00:51:04,960 --> 00:51:06,996
There's a good boy.

765
00:51:09,920 --> 00:51:12,354
- Ed, can you pull over?
- 2 seconds.

766
00:51:14,880 --> 00:51:17,474
- Ah! Ed, please pull over.
- What for?

767
00:51:17,520 --> 00:51:20,318
- Just pull over!
- All right.

768
00:51:25,720 --> 00:51:27,119
Whoa, momma!

769
00:51:27,160 --> 00:51:30,470
- What the hell are you doing?
- Chill out. Everyone's all right.

770
00:51:30,520 --> 00:51:32,590
Stop telling me to chill out!

771
00:51:33,560 --> 00:51:36,996
- And everybody is not all right.
- (Liz) What's wrong?

772
00:51:37,040 --> 00:51:39,554
Mum, it's Philip, he's gone.

773
00:51:39,600 --> 00:51:42,068
- Where's he gone?
- Mum, he's dead.

774
00:51:43,080 --> 00:51:45,275
No, he isn't.

775
00:51:45,320 --> 00:51:47,231
Get out!

776
00:51:48,600 --> 00:51:50,795
Jesus!

777
00:51:50,840 --> 00:51:53,991
- Get it open!
- Ed, get the child locks!

778
00:51:54,040 --> 00:51:56,031
(Di) Quick!

779
00:51:56,080 --> 00:51:58,310
(Music starts again)

780
00:51:58,360 --> 00:52:00,271
- The child lock!
- Ed!

781
00:52:19,280 --> 00:52:21,350
- Now what?
- We keep moving.

782
00:52:21,400 --> 00:52:25,029
- (Liz) How do we get Philip out the car?
- We haven't got time.

783
00:52:25,080 --> 00:52:27,719
- We can't leave your dad.
- He's not my dad!

784
00:52:27,760 --> 00:52:29,716
Mum, he was, but he's not any more.

785
00:52:29,760 --> 00:52:34,038
- I really think we could...
- That's not your husband in there. OK?

786
00:52:34,080 --> 00:52:38,278
It looks like him but there is nothing
of the man you loved in that car.

787
00:52:38,320 --> 00:52:40,470
(Turns music off)

788
00:52:40,520 --> 00:52:42,556
Let's go, shall we?

789
00:52:42,600 --> 00:52:44,830
You're not suggesting we walk?

790
00:52:46,760 --> 00:52:50,799
- Everybody OK?
- (Ed) Yeah, we're having a whale of a time.

791
00:52:50,840 --> 00:52:53,912
Maybe we should all hold hands,
make a crocodile?

792
00:52:53,960 --> 00:52:55,916
Do you know where we're going?

793
00:52:55,960 --> 00:52:58,349
- David, come on.
- Sorry.

794
00:52:58,400 --> 00:53:00,709
- Do you, though?
- Yeah, totally.

795
00:53:00,760 --> 00:53:02,273
Are we close?

796
00:53:07,800 --> 00:53:10,155
We're pretty close.

797
00:53:10,200 --> 00:53:12,998
- Is your mum gonna be OK?
- Yeah, I hope so.

798
00:53:13,040 --> 00:53:15,838
- Did you contact your folks?
- They're in Antigua.

799
00:53:15,880 --> 00:53:18,758
- Do you think this is happening there?
- I hope not.

800
00:53:18,800 --> 00:53:21,758
About last night.
I know loads of things were said but...

801
00:53:21,800 --> 00:53:24,473
- You said this wasn't about us.
- No, it's not.

802
00:53:24,520 --> 00:53:27,318
- You said it was about survival.
- It is, but...

803
00:53:27,360 --> 00:53:32,559
You're not just trying to prove something?
I meant everything I said last night.

804
00:53:32,600 --> 00:53:34,716
(Distant screaming and shouting)

805
00:53:34,760 --> 00:53:37,957
- Maybe this isn't the best time to talk.
- OK.

806
00:53:39,000 --> 00:53:40,558
Shaun.

807
00:53:40,600 --> 00:53:41,999
Yvonne.

808
00:53:42,040 --> 00:53:44,713
- How's it going?
- Er, surviving.

809
00:53:44,760 --> 00:53:47,228
Hey, Liz. Long time no see.

810
00:53:47,280 --> 00:53:48,918
Hey, Yvonne.

811
00:53:48,960 --> 00:53:51,713
Erm...this is my boyfriend, Declan.

812
00:53:51,760 --> 00:53:53,751
Erm...my friends Mark, Maggie,

813
00:53:53,800 --> 00:53:57,156
- my mum and my cousin Tom.
- All right.

814
00:53:57,200 --> 00:53:59,634
This is Shaun and his girlfriend Liz.

815
00:53:59,680 --> 00:54:02,558
- They've split up, actually.
- Oh, really?

816
00:54:02,600 --> 00:54:04,670
- Yeah.
- That's a shame.

817
00:54:04,720 --> 00:54:07,632
We should scoot.
Have you got somewhere you're going?

818
00:54:07,680 --> 00:54:11,070
- Yeah, we're going to the Winchester.
- The pub?

819
00:54:12,880 --> 00:54:15,553
- Yeah.
- Right, well. Good luck!

820
00:54:21,200 --> 00:54:22,918
(Both) Hi.

821
00:54:22,960 --> 00:54:24,393
(Both) Hello.

822
00:54:24,440 --> 00:54:25,509
Hi.

823
00:54:25,560 --> 00:54:27,278
(Both) Hello.

824
00:54:27,320 --> 00:54:28,912
(Both) All right.

825
00:54:30,440 --> 00:54:32,829
See? The Winchester's just over there.

826
00:54:32,880 --> 00:54:35,189
- Over where?
- Over there.

827
00:54:35,240 --> 00:54:37,708
Just over there, over the 20 garden fences?

828
00:54:37,760 --> 00:54:39,512
What's the matter, David?

829
00:54:41,080 --> 00:54:43,196
Never taken a short cut before?

830
00:54:59,360 --> 00:55:00,952
Shaun.

831
00:55:01,000 --> 00:55:03,673
I'm sure Jill and Derek live round here.

832
00:55:17,120 --> 00:55:21,113
Now, the Winchester
is just over that fence, all right?

833
00:55:21,160 --> 00:55:24,311
Everyone stay where they are, I'll...
Are we all here?

834
00:55:24,360 --> 00:55:27,875
- 1, 2, 3, 4, 5. Yes.
- There's 6 of us.

835
00:55:27,920 --> 00:55:30,115
- (Screaming)
- Mum!

836
00:55:32,720 --> 00:55:34,711
I'm coming!

837
00:55:34,760 --> 00:55:37,354
Mum, are you OK? Are you OK?

838
00:55:37,400 --> 00:55:40,119
I don't think Jill and Derek do live here.

839
00:55:42,400 --> 00:55:43,913
Shaun?

840
00:55:47,240 --> 00:55:49,356
Are you all right?

841
00:55:49,840 --> 00:55:52,035
(Footsteps and scuffling)

842
00:56:06,000 --> 00:56:08,639
What are you doing?

843
00:56:10,640 --> 00:56:12,631
Shaun!

844
00:56:15,480 --> 00:56:17,232
Yes!

845
00:56:18,800 --> 00:56:20,950
No, that's rubbish.

846
00:56:28,120 --> 00:56:30,236
- Ooh!
- Yes!

847
00:56:31,920 --> 00:56:34,150
Feel free to step in any time.

848
00:56:34,200 --> 00:56:37,192
- You did all right.
- I didn't want to cramp your style.

849
00:56:37,240 --> 00:56:39,310
I'm so sorry about that.

850
00:56:41,040 --> 00:56:43,076
Right.

851
00:56:44,320 --> 00:56:48,916
OK, everyone stay where they are.
I'm gonna check if the coast is clear.

852
00:56:57,400 --> 00:56:59,391
- Is it clear?
- No.

853
00:56:59,440 --> 00:57:01,510
- How many?
- Lots.

854
00:57:11,280 --> 00:57:14,192
Oh, well, that is just great.

855
00:57:14,240 --> 00:57:16,356
There are a fair few of them, yes.

856
00:57:16,400 --> 00:57:19,631
I trust Shaun has another genius scheme
up his sleeve?

857
00:57:19,680 --> 00:57:21,796
This is hardly constructive, David!

858
00:57:21,840 --> 00:57:25,515
- We should have stayed at the flat.
- Why didn't you?

859
00:57:25,560 --> 00:57:29,758
Because... Because, because of...
Captain Wow.

860
00:57:29,800 --> 00:57:33,076
- Will you stop it?
- We'll get nowhere moaning.

861
00:57:33,120 --> 00:57:35,350
(Low groaning)

862
00:57:41,360 --> 00:57:44,397
Right, let's all shake out.
Get nice and limber.

863
00:57:44,440 --> 00:57:46,510
Or not.

864
00:57:46,560 --> 00:57:50,155
Take another look at the way he moves.
Remember, very limp.

865
00:57:50,200 --> 00:57:55,479
Almost like sleepwalking. Look at the face,
it's vacant with a hint of sadness.

866
00:57:55,520 --> 00:57:57,715
Like a drunk who's lost a bet.

867
00:57:57,760 --> 00:57:59,751
OK, let's try, shall we? Liz.

868
00:58:00,720 --> 00:58:03,359
(Groans)

869
00:58:03,400 --> 00:58:07,439
Nice. Good vocal work.
OK. Barbara, that's excellent.

870
00:58:07,480 --> 00:58:09,869
Sorry, dear, I was miles away.

871
00:58:09,920 --> 00:58:12,559
- D-Daffs.
- Uh.

872
00:58:12,600 --> 00:58:14,511
- Come on!
- Urgh.

873
00:58:14,560 --> 00:58:17,836
It's mournful, sorrowful,
you're dead and you hate it. Go.

874
00:58:17,880 --> 00:58:19,552
Uuurgh.

875
00:58:19,600 --> 00:58:22,433
- Much better. Ed.
- I'll do it on the night.

876
00:58:22,480 --> 00:58:24,710
This is the night!

877
00:58:24,760 --> 00:58:27,069
- What is that?
- What about yours?

878
00:58:27,120 --> 00:58:29,998
Who died and made you
fucking king of the zombies?

879
00:58:30,040 --> 00:58:31,632
Don't...

880
00:58:31,680 --> 00:58:34,194
(Groans)

881
00:58:34,240 --> 00:58:36,151
Yeah, that's pretty good.

882
00:58:36,200 --> 00:58:41,877
Right, let's all try together, shall we?
1, 2, 3.

883
00:59:33,960 --> 00:59:35,791
Go, go, go, go.

884
00:59:37,960 --> 00:59:40,349
Shit! Get round me, get round me!

885
00:59:40,400 --> 00:59:44,678
John? John, Bernie, are you there?
It's Shaun and Ed. We come in all the time.

886
00:59:45,520 --> 00:59:47,715
- They can hear you.
- We do the quiz.

887
00:59:47,760 --> 00:59:49,239
- They know.
- Stay in character!

888
00:59:49,280 --> 00:59:52,397
- I can't see them.
- Shaun, we have to get inside.

889
00:59:52,440 --> 00:59:54,954
- Break the window.
- We'll be exposed!

890
00:59:55,000 --> 00:59:57,673
- Break the window!
- Is there another way in?

891
00:59:57,720 --> 00:59:59,676
- Yeah, there's...
- (Mobile)

892
01:00:00,640 --> 01:00:03,029
2 seconds. Hey, Noodle.

893
01:00:03,080 --> 01:00:05,719
<i>- 'All right?'</i>
- Yeah, man, I can't talk now.</i>

894
01:00:05,760 --> 01:00:08,513
<i>- 'You get anything yet?'</i>
- I got nothing.</i>

895
01:00:08,560 --> 01:00:11,393
I'm in the middle of something.
Yeah, it's weird.

896
01:00:11,440 --> 01:00:15,149
- Oi! What are you doing?
- What are you doing? You stupid moron.

897
01:00:15,200 --> 01:00:17,668
- Fuck off.
- You fuck off!.

898
01:00:17,720 --> 01:00:21,110
Fuck fucking off!. I've spent an entire life...

899
01:00:21,160 --> 01:00:24,277
Look at me. I've spent my entire life
sticking up for you

900
01:00:24,320 --> 01:00:27,471
and all you ever do is fuck things up
and make me look stupid.

901
01:00:27,520 --> 01:00:30,512
I'm not gonna let you do it any more.
Not today!

902
01:00:30,560 --> 01:00:32,471
Shaun.

903
01:00:32,520 --> 01:00:33,748
Oh.

904
01:00:40,840 --> 01:00:43,559
You were saying about another way in?

905
01:00:43,600 --> 01:00:45,636
Yeah, there's a...

906
01:00:45,680 --> 01:00:48,194
What are you doing?

907
01:00:49,320 --> 01:00:52,437
- (Shaun) No!
- Get inside.

908
01:00:52,480 --> 01:00:56,109
No, they'll follow us.
Keep up the act, I'll have to do something.

909
01:00:56,160 --> 01:00:59,994
- What do you mean do something?
- Hello, hello, over here!

910
01:01:00,040 --> 01:01:04,033
Come on, that's it.
Come on, that's it, over here!

911
01:01:04,080 --> 01:01:06,992
Over here! Come on. Oh, bollocks.

912
01:01:07,040 --> 01:01:09,918
- Wait till I've gone then get inside.
- Gone where?

913
01:01:09,960 --> 01:01:15,557
I won't be long, I promise. Come on,
you pasty-faced fuckers, let's go! Follow me.

914
01:01:15,600 --> 01:01:18,910
Come on, this way, that's it!

915
01:01:18,960 --> 01:01:22,714
Come on. This way, follow me.
Come on, follow me.

916
01:01:22,760 --> 01:01:26,196
Come and get it. It's a running buffet.

917
01:01:26,240 --> 01:01:28,356
All you can eat!

918
01:01:28,400 --> 01:01:30,391
Shall we go in, then?

919
01:01:38,240 --> 01:01:41,630
- Come on, Barbara. Leave those.
- I think they're for me.

920
01:02:00,720 --> 01:02:03,359
- He's been gone a good 20 minutes.
- 17.

921
01:02:03,560 --> 01:02:08,793
Either way, we need to think about blocking
up this window. We're totally exposed.

922
01:02:08,840 --> 01:02:12,276
- How will Shaun get back in?
- I'm sure he'll knock.

923
01:02:13,880 --> 01:02:16,713
- Let's get some lights on.
- David, wait!

924
01:02:18,000 --> 01:02:20,468
- Power's off.
- That's a good thing.

925
01:02:20,520 --> 01:02:23,830
- We mustn't advertise our whereabouts.
- No, of course not.

926
01:02:23,880 --> 01:02:27,714
- Do we, David?
- No, of course not, Lizzie.

927
01:02:27,760 --> 01:02:29,671
I'm just being proactive.

928
01:02:29,720 --> 01:02:33,952
There's no lights, no power.
And there's a hole in the window.

929
01:02:34,000 --> 01:02:37,515
- You did that, you twat.
- Somebody had to do something!

930
01:02:37,560 --> 01:02:41,314
We were in a spot of bother. Somebody
has to take control of the situation

931
01:02:41,360 --> 01:02:45,512
and if none of you are prepared
to accept that responsibility

932
01:02:45,560 --> 01:02:48,597
then perhaps...I should.

933
01:02:48,640 --> 01:02:51,916
- Will Shaun be gone long?
- (Liz) He'll be back soon.

934
01:02:51,960 --> 01:02:54,758
- How do you know?
- I don't think he'd leave us.

935
01:02:54,800 --> 01:03:00,796
Wouldn't he? How can you trust a man
you binned for being unreliable?

936
01:03:00,840 --> 01:03:05,277
A man whose idea of a romantic nightspot
is also an impenetrable fortress.

937
01:03:05,320 --> 01:03:08,312
This is a pub! We are in a pub!
What are we going to do?

938
01:03:08,360 --> 01:03:10,874
I could get a round in.

939
01:03:10,920 --> 01:03:14,549
Let's just wait for Shaun. We'll barricade
the window when he gets back.

940
01:03:14,600 --> 01:03:17,558
What then? How long?
Days? Weeks? A month?

941
01:03:17,600 --> 01:03:19,716
- What are we going to eat?
- Toasties!

942
01:03:19,760 --> 01:03:23,230
- There's a Breville out back.
- Great. Saved by nibbles.

943
01:03:23,280 --> 01:03:25,510
Must be why Shaun took us here
before he left.

944
01:03:25,560 --> 01:03:29,519
- He's coming back!
- Why? Because he promised?

945
01:03:29,560 --> 01:03:34,429
If he does, do you think his master plan
will be anything more than eating peanuts?

946
01:03:34,480 --> 01:03:37,517
Is he just gonna stroll in
and suddenly everything's OK?

947
01:03:37,560 --> 01:03:41,951
I don't know, David!
I don't know any more than you do.

948
01:03:42,000 --> 01:03:46,391
But what I do know is that we're here now
and we have to make the best of it.

949
01:03:48,040 --> 01:03:50,873
- Ed, get me a double vodka.
- Right you are.

950
01:03:50,920 --> 01:03:53,912
I'll have a drink too.
Would you like a drink, Barbara?

951
01:03:53,960 --> 01:03:56,076
- Hello.
- Right, great, fuck it.

952
01:03:56,120 --> 01:03:59,635
We'll have a party
and get completely smashed.

953
01:03:59,680 --> 01:04:03,275
We've got our nibbles.
We've got our Mini Cheddars.

954
01:04:03,320 --> 01:04:06,756
- David!
- We got Twiglets. Oh, look, hog lumps.

955
01:04:11,920 --> 01:04:13,433
Pickle!

956
01:04:13,480 --> 01:04:15,152
Hello, Mum. You all right?

957
01:04:15,200 --> 01:04:17,191
- Everybody OK?
- Yeah.

958
01:04:17,240 --> 01:04:19,390
- Any sign of John and Bernie?
- No.

959
01:04:19,440 --> 01:04:21,590
- Check upstairs?
- It's locked.

960
01:04:21,640 --> 01:04:24,074
- Phones?
- Dead. Same as the power.

961
01:04:24,120 --> 01:04:27,999
- OK...
- Nice of you to join us.

962
01:04:28,040 --> 01:04:30,554
Yeah, well, I promised, didn't l?

963
01:04:36,080 --> 01:04:38,833
How did you lose them?

964
01:04:40,360 --> 01:04:43,875
I just gave them the slip.
Wasn't difficult. They're not all that.

965
01:04:43,920 --> 01:04:46,593
- Well, how did you get in?
- The back door.

966
01:04:46,640 --> 01:04:49,029
I tried to tell you
before you smashed the window.

967
01:04:49,080 --> 01:04:52,311
But it wasn't me blowing our cover
by arguing with my boyfriend.

968
01:04:52,360 --> 01:04:55,989
- He's not my boyfriend.
- Might be a bit warm, the cooler's off.

969
01:04:56,040 --> 01:04:58,076
Thanks, babe.

970
01:04:59,520 --> 01:05:01,431
So, what's the plan, then?

971
01:05:03,840 --> 01:05:06,513
Would anyone like a peanut?

972
01:05:15,520 --> 01:05:17,636
Why don't you do your Clyde?

973
01:05:17,680 --> 01:05:20,592
Has anyone seen
Every Which Way But Loose?

974
01:05:20,640 --> 01:05:23,473
Ed does the most amazing
impression of the orang-utan.

975
01:05:23,520 --> 01:05:26,114
- No, it's not.
- It is. Come on. Do it.

976
01:05:26,160 --> 01:05:28,879
- No, no.
- But it's brilliant. Come on.

977
01:05:28,920 --> 01:05:31,957
- You've built it up too much.
- No, just do it.

978
01:05:32,000 --> 01:05:34,798
Everyone wants to see it.
We could do with a laugh.

979
01:05:34,840 --> 01:05:37,308
Do it, do it, do it, do it. Come on, do it.

980
01:05:37,360 --> 01:05:39,396
I'm not a performing monkey.

981
01:05:41,760 --> 01:05:44,991
- The power's on.
- It's not, I tried it earlier.

982
01:05:45,040 --> 01:05:48,828
The streetlights are on.
I'll flip the fuses, we can watch television.

983
01:05:48,880 --> 01:05:52,555
- What about the lights?
- Yes. Don't advertise our whereabouts.

984
01:05:52,600 --> 01:05:56,275
The lights are on a separate circuit.
Just flip the mains breakers.

985
01:05:56,320 --> 01:05:58,595
It's quite simple, David.

986
01:06:25,360 --> 01:06:27,920
- Is that it?
- (Liz) That's it.

987
01:06:38,400 --> 01:06:40,834
(Hammering on the door)

988
01:06:53,080 --> 01:06:56,436
Liz, erm...have you got a quid?

989
01:06:57,480 --> 01:06:59,277
Erm...

990
01:07:01,160 --> 01:07:02,718
Yeah.

991
01:07:07,080 --> 01:07:09,275
Never anything on, is there?

992
01:07:13,680 --> 01:07:15,398
What?

993
01:07:17,320 --> 01:07:21,233
- I think we might have a bit of a problem.
- What do you mean?

994
01:07:25,040 --> 01:07:28,749
- They followed me.
- I thought you said you gave them the slip.

995
01:07:28,800 --> 01:07:31,075
Yeah.

996
01:07:31,120 --> 01:07:35,557
(Whispering) Well, we'll just have to be
extra quiet then, won't we?

997
01:07:36,920 --> 01:07:38,911
What?

998
01:07:38,960 --> 01:07:40,598
(Loud jingle on fruit machine)

999
01:07:40,640 --> 01:07:42,995
Ed, no!

1000
01:07:43,040 --> 01:07:45,076
Turn it off!.

1001
01:07:53,680 --> 01:07:55,955
(Windows rattling)

1002
01:07:56,000 --> 01:07:59,231
(Low groaning)

1003
01:08:15,280 --> 01:08:17,157
Shit!

1004
01:08:17,200 --> 01:08:19,794
- Where the hell did he come from?
- I dunno.

1005
01:08:19,840 --> 01:08:23,515
(# Queen: Don't Stop Me Now)

1006
01:08:23,560 --> 01:08:26,472
- Who put this on?
- It's on random.

1007
01:08:26,520 --> 01:08:29,637
Dianne, get Mum somewhere safe.
David, kill the Queen.

1008
01:08:29,680 --> 01:08:31,398
- What?!
- The jukebox!

1009
01:08:31,440 --> 01:08:34,034
- Liz, Ed, grab a weapon.
- What about the rifle?

1010
01:08:34,080 --> 01:08:36,071
- Cocktails?
- What do you mean?

1011
01:08:36,120 --> 01:08:39,476
The flaming spirits
Get a rag in, light it.

1012
01:08:39,520 --> 01:08:42,478
- But the whole place could go up.
- What, then?

1013
01:08:42,520 --> 01:08:44,397
How about pool?

