<i>- # Cos I'm having... #</i>
- John, it's time at the bar.</i>

1017
01:08:52,800 --> 01:08:56,475
<i># I'm a shooting star
leaping through the sky like a tiger</i>

1018
01:08:56,520 --> 01:08:59,990
<i># Defying the laws of gravity</i>

1019
01:09:00,040 --> 01:09:04,158
<i># I'm a racing car passing by
like Lady Godiva</i>

1020
01:09:04,200 --> 01:09:06,555
<i># I'm gonna go, go, go</i>

1021
01:09:06,600 --> 01:09:09,034
<i># There's no stopping me</i>

1022
01:09:09,080 --> 01:09:11,275
<i># I'm burning through the sky...</i>

1023
01:09:11,320 --> 01:09:14,118
- I can't find the switches!
- Then get the fuses!

1024
01:09:14,520 --> 01:09:16,397
<i># That's why they call me Mister Fahrenheit</i>

1025
01:09:16,440 --> 01:09:18,556
<i># I'm travelling at the speed of light</i>

1026
01:09:18,600 --> 01:09:22,354
<i># I wanna make
a supersonic man out of you</i>

1027
01:09:22,400 --> 01:09:24,436
<i># Don't stop me now</i>

1028
01:09:24,480 --> 01:09:26,516
<i># I'm having such a good time</i>

1029
01:09:26,560 --> 01:09:28,551
<i># I'm having a ball</i>

1030
01:09:28,600 --> 01:09:30,431
<i># Don't stop me now</i>

1031
01:09:30,480 --> 01:09:32,550
<i># If you wanna have a good time</i>

1032
01:09:32,600 --> 01:09:34,397
<i># Just give me a call</i>

1033
01:09:34,440 --> 01:09:36,954
<i># Don't stop me now
cos I'm having a good time</i>

1034
01:09:37,000 --> 01:09:38,797
<i># Don't stop me now</i>

1035
01:09:38,840 --> 01:09:44,358
<i># Yes I'm having a good time
I don't wanna stop at all</i>

1036
01:09:44,400 --> 01:09:48,279
<i>- # I'm a rocket ship on my way to Mars...</i>
- Why is Queen still on?</i>

1037
01:09:48,320 --> 01:09:50,754
- We have a situation!
- I know!

1038
01:09:51,840 --> 01:09:53,990
- Fuck this. 2 seconds.
- Ed!

1039
01:09:54,040 --> 01:09:55,598
(Liz) Oi!

1040
01:09:55,640 --> 01:10:00,270
<i># Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, explode</i>

1041
01:10:00,320 --> 01:10:03,312
<i># I'm burning through the sky, yeah...</i>

1042
01:10:03,360 --> 01:10:05,112
Shaun!

1043
01:10:05,160 --> 01:10:07,230
<i>#..call me Mister Fahrenheit...</i>

1044
01:10:07,280 --> 01:10:08,759
No!

1045
01:10:10,600 --> 01:10:12,795
Yes! Yes! In the head!

1046
01:10:15,480 --> 01:10:17,277
Ooow!

1047
01:10:17,320 --> 01:10:18,833
Shauny!

1048
01:10:18,880 --> 01:10:20,950
<i># Don't stop me
Ooh, ooh, ooh</i>

1049
01:10:21,000 --> 01:10:24,788
<i># Don't stop me, don't stop me
good time, good time</i>

1050
01:10:24,840 --> 01:10:26,717
<i># Don't stop me... #</i>

1051
01:10:34,080 --> 01:10:36,389
Why didn't you just shoot him, man?

1052
01:10:37,760 --> 01:10:39,910
Ed, for the last time, it's...

1053
01:10:43,360 --> 01:10:47,433
I fucking knew it!
What did I tell you? Big Al was right.

1054
01:10:47,480 --> 01:10:49,277
OK.

1055
01:10:52,800 --> 01:10:54,756
But dogs can look up.

1056
01:10:57,720 --> 01:11:00,280
- Has anyone fired a gun before?
- Oh, yeah.

1057
01:11:00,320 --> 01:11:02,117
- Apart from Ed?
- I'm a pacifist.

1058
01:11:02,160 --> 01:11:04,879
- Apart from David and Ed?
- What was Ed's experience?

1059
01:11:04,920 --> 01:11:08,117
- He shot his sister in the leg.
- I think you should do it.

1060
01:11:08,160 --> 01:11:11,277
- We should all do it.
- How can 5 people operate 1 gun?

1061
01:11:11,320 --> 01:11:14,153
- No one has any experience. We've got...
- 29.

1062
01:11:14,200 --> 01:11:16,156
- 29 bullets.
- Call them shells.

1063
01:11:16,200 --> 01:11:19,192
29 shells. I need someone
to help me reload,

1064
01:11:19,240 --> 01:11:21,674
everyone else to look out. I will fire.

1065
01:11:21,720 --> 01:11:26,555
As Bertrand Russell said the only thing
that will redeem mankind is co-operation.

1066
01:11:26,600 --> 01:11:28,670
I think we can all appreciate that now.

1067
01:11:28,720 --> 01:11:32,235
- Was that on a beer mat?
- Yeah, it was Guinness Extra Cold.

1068
01:11:32,280 --> 01:11:34,111
- I won't say anything.
- Thanks.

1069
01:11:34,160 --> 01:11:35,639
(Crashing)

1070
01:11:35,680 --> 01:11:38,717
- They want to come in.
- Get Mum out of the way.

1071
01:11:38,760 --> 01:11:42,309
David, Dianne, let's go.
Ed, give me some shells.

1072
01:11:44,480 --> 01:11:46,710
- Barbara.
- Oh, hello.

1073
01:11:46,760 --> 01:11:49,718
- Would you like to come with me?
- That'd be lovely.

1074
01:11:51,080 --> 01:11:56,154
It's nice to meet you, finally.
Shaun's always talking about you.

1075
01:11:56,200 --> 01:11:58,191
- Really?
- Yeah.

1076
01:11:58,240 --> 01:12:00,151
- Ah!
- Barbara?

1077
01:12:01,520 --> 01:12:03,988
Are you all right?

1078
01:12:04,040 --> 01:12:05,837
I've got something for you.

1079
01:12:06,880 --> 01:12:10,509
Shaun's father gave me this.
Shaun's real father, I mean.

1080
01:12:10,560 --> 01:12:13,996
- I'd like you to have it.
- Barbara, Shaun and I have...

1081
01:12:14,040 --> 01:12:16,918
It seems only right.

1082
01:12:30,640 --> 01:12:32,596
I didn't want to say anything.

1083
01:12:32,640 --> 01:12:34,756
I thought Shaun would be worried.

1084
01:12:36,480 --> 01:12:38,152
Liz!

1085
01:12:38,200 --> 01:12:39,918
Here they come!

1086
01:12:41,200 --> 01:12:43,395
- Stay behind me!
- There's one!

1087
01:12:43,440 --> 01:12:45,795
Sorry, we're closed!

1088
01:12:45,840 --> 01:12:48,070
- The safety!
- That happened to me on stage.

1089
01:12:48,120 --> 01:12:50,190
Cock it!

1090
01:12:57,040 --> 01:12:58,758
- There!
- Where?

1091
01:12:58,800 --> 01:13:00,711
3 o'clock!

1092
01:13:05,760 --> 01:13:09,275
- Oh! Over there again. Quarter to 12.
- What?

1093
01:13:09,320 --> 01:13:11,390
- 11:45!
- Keep it simple!

1094
01:13:12,520 --> 01:13:14,272
Top left!

1095
01:13:16,360 --> 01:13:18,476
- Reload.
- I'm on it!

1096
01:13:18,520 --> 01:13:20,556
Come on, come on.

1097
01:13:23,840 --> 01:13:25,592
Nice shot.

1098
01:13:25,640 --> 01:13:28,200
OK, David, Dianne,
let's block up this window!

1099
01:13:28,240 --> 01:13:30,356
Ed, take over a sec.

1100
01:13:30,520 --> 01:13:33,671
- What is it? What's wrong?
- (Liz) Shaun, I'm so sorry.

1101
01:13:33,720 --> 01:13:37,633
- Mum, what's wrong?
- I didn't want to be a bother.

1102
01:13:40,440 --> 01:13:43,750
- Mum, I don't understand.
- The man in his pyjamas.

1103
01:13:43,800 --> 01:13:46,917
I didn't want to say anything,
I thought you'd be upset.

1104
01:13:46,960 --> 01:13:49,918
No, you should've said.

1105
01:13:49,960 --> 01:13:52,997
- Take over a sec.
- What's going on?

1106
01:13:53,040 --> 01:13:55,429
- What's up?
- What the hell's going on?

1107
01:13:55,480 --> 01:13:58,597
- Barbara's hurt!
- Just take over a minute.

1108
01:13:58,640 --> 01:14:00,471
(Ed) Jesus.

1109
01:14:00,520 --> 01:14:02,556
(Di) I know first aid.

1110
01:14:02,600 --> 01:14:05,433
Just hang on. Mum!

1111
01:14:05,480 --> 01:14:07,869
- Mum.
- Is she...?

1112
01:14:07,920 --> 01:14:10,150
Just hold on, Mum, you're gonna be fine.

1113
01:14:10,200 --> 01:14:13,237
- I never thanked you.
- For what?

1114
01:14:14,520 --> 01:14:18,274
For these. "To a wonderful mum."

1115
01:14:20,160 --> 01:14:22,833
It's been a funny sort of day, hasn't it?

1116
01:14:23,840 --> 01:14:26,638
Oh, no, no! Mum, come on.

1117
01:14:26,680 --> 01:14:28,796
Stop it, stop it, stop it.

1118
01:14:28,840 --> 01:14:31,115
(Sobbing) Mum. Please don't go.

1119
01:14:39,400 --> 01:14:42,153
(Gun cocks)

1120
01:14:42,200 --> 01:14:45,078
- What are you doing?
- We have to deal with her.

1121
01:14:45,120 --> 01:14:47,634
- Daffs!
- For Christ's sake!

1122
01:14:47,680 --> 01:14:49,955
- She's gonna come back!
- She's not going anywhere.

1123
01:14:50,000 --> 01:14:52,309
- She'll change.
- She's my mum!

1124
01:14:52,360 --> 01:14:54,999
- She's a zombie.
- Don't say that.

1125
01:14:56,000 --> 01:14:58,275
Move aside. I'm gonna count to 3.

1126
01:14:58,320 --> 01:15:00,311
1...

1127
01:15:00,360 --> 01:15:01,759
2...

1128
01:15:01,800 --> 01:15:02,994
3!

1129
01:15:03,040 --> 01:15:05,713
- Don't point that gun at my mum!
- Calm down.

1130
01:15:05,760 --> 01:15:08,194
Don't point that gun at Barbara!

1131
01:15:08,240 --> 01:15:10,595
- Ed, don't exacerbate things!
- What's that mean?

1132
01:15:10,640 --> 01:15:12,915
- This isn't exactly fair.
- Here.

1133
01:15:12,960 --> 01:15:14,757
- Thank you.
- It's OK.

1134
01:15:15,960 --> 01:15:18,758
Please, can we just stop
and think about this?

1135
01:15:18,800 --> 01:15:20,597
Tell him to put the gun down!

1136
01:15:20,640 --> 01:15:22,790
She's gonna change. You know I'm right.

1137
01:15:22,840 --> 01:15:27,960
And when she does, she'll kill all of us.
That's what your ex can't seem to realise.

1138
01:15:28,000 --> 01:15:31,151
That's what this is about, isn't it?
He doesn't like me!

1139
01:15:31,200 --> 01:15:33,589
He's always hated me
and now he wants to shoot my mum.

1140
01:15:33,640 --> 01:15:37,235
- She's not...
- You've never thought I was good enough.

1141
01:15:37,280 --> 01:15:40,397
- What?
- We all know you're in love with Liz.

1142
01:15:40,440 --> 01:15:42,795
- That is not true.
- (Shaun) Yes it is!

1143
01:15:42,840 --> 01:15:44,796
- That is not true.
- (Di) Yes it is.

1144
01:15:44,840 --> 01:15:47,434
- What?
- I know you only hung out with me

1145
01:15:47,480 --> 01:15:52,270
to get close to Liz and when she knocked
you back, I was there to pick up the pieces.

1146
01:15:52,320 --> 01:15:55,915
I've come to terms with that, Daffs,
why can't you?

1147
01:15:55,960 --> 01:15:59,191
Lizzie, I want you to know
that my feelings for you...

1148
01:15:59,240 --> 01:16:03,233
David! There are slightly more
pressing matters at hand here.

1149
01:16:03,280 --> 01:16:07,273
- Like "Daffs" pointing a gun at my mum.
- I'm not being unreasonable, "Pickle".

1150
01:16:07,320 --> 01:16:10,278
- Christ, she's not dead!
- She's finished.

1151
01:16:10,320 --> 01:16:12,356
For a hero, you're quite a hypocrite.

1152
01:16:12,400 --> 01:16:15,039
You've gone from
a chartered accountant to Charlton Heston.

1153
01:16:15,080 --> 01:16:16,832
I'm not a chartered accountant.

1154
01:16:16,880 --> 01:16:18,996
- Well, you look like one.
- Yeah.

1155
01:16:19,040 --> 01:16:21,952
- I'm a lecturer.
- You're a twat.

1156
01:16:22,000 --> 01:16:25,549
She's not your mum.
In a minute she'll be just another zombie.

1157
01:16:25,600 --> 01:16:28,672
- Don't say that.
- We're not using the Z word.

1158
01:16:28,720 --> 01:16:32,508
Please can we just calm the fuck down!

1159
01:16:34,040 --> 01:16:37,510
Now, I can see what David is trying to say...

1160
01:16:37,560 --> 01:16:39,755
- Thank you.
- Even if he is being a twat.

1161
01:16:39,800 --> 01:16:41,552
Yep.

1162
01:16:41,600 --> 01:16:44,398
And, Shaun... Shaun, look at me.

1163
01:16:47,040 --> 01:16:50,510
I can't begin to imagine
how hard this must be for you

1164
01:16:50,560 --> 01:16:52,915
but we can't afford to fall apart.

1165
01:16:54,040 --> 01:16:56,759
Shaun, babe...

1166
01:16:56,800 --> 01:16:59,712
I know you don't wanna hear this...

1167
01:17:17,320 --> 01:17:19,311
You do it.

1168
01:17:28,840 --> 01:17:30,876
I'm sorry, Mum.

1169
01:17:32,200 --> 01:17:34,475
